This file is not distributed with the module. It outlines some notes for
developers readying a set of files for distribution.

Subversion CHECKOUT:
$ svn co https://module-install-custominstallationpath.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ Module-Install-CustomInstallationPath

Checklist for a release:
- Be sure to add new test cases for new features
- Make sure version number increases.
- Add version changes to README and CHANGES, anonymizing the notes in the README.
- Add new module dependencies to Makefile.PL, and update README
- Update MANIFEST and MANIFEST.SKIP if necessary.
  $ make distcheck
- Test your distribution:
  $ make realclean
  $ perl Makefile.PL
  $ make
  $ make test
- After the tests have passed, make the distribution file:
  $ make dist
- Install the distribution file elsewhere to test it.
  $ scp Module-Install-CustomInstallationPath-X.XX.tar.gz coppit@linux.sourceforge.net:.
  $ ssh -l coppit linux.sourceforge.net
  $ tar xvfz Module-Install-*.tar.gz
  $ cd Module-Install-CustomInstallationPath-X.XX
  $ perl Makefile.PL
  $ make
  $ make test
- Upload to CPAN:
    http://pause.perl.org/pause/authenquery
  or
    cpan-upload Module-Install-CustomInstallationPath-X.XX.tar.gz
- Upload to server:
  $ scp Module-Install-CustomInstallationPath-X.XX.tar.gz dcoppit@coppit.org:www/coppit/html/code
- Update webpage:
  $ ssh -t dcoppit@coppit.org 'vim www/coppit/html/code/index.php'
- Announce it to comp.lang.perl.announce
- Copy current code to old in devel
  $ rm -rf old; rsync -r --cvs-exclude --exclude=.svn * old
- Check in code:
  $ svn commit
- Tag the release for easy retrieval later
  $ cvs cp https://module-install-custominstallationpath.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ https://module-install-custominstallationpath.googlecode.com/svn/tags/v5.20.0
